<item>
            <title>[FLINK-2707] Set state checkpointer before default state for PartitionedStreamOperatorState</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-2707</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the default state is set before the passed StateCheckpointer instance for operator states.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What currently happens because of this is that the default value is serialized with Java serialization and then deserialized on the opstate.value() call using the StateCheckpointer most likely causing a failure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can be trivially fixed by swaping the order of the 2 calls.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
